  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment covering verification, validation, and applicability activities. Seven factors are formally assessed and all are reported as meeting or exceeding required levels; six factors are scoped out as not applicable at MRL 2. The overall assessment team concluded that the body of evidence supports a Medium assurance level and the use of the model for the stated COU.",
