      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification level 1 required: documented benchmark results available from solver vendor.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent passes published NASA turbulence model benchmarks and the vendor-supplied laminar pipe-flow and lid-driven cavity verification cases. Results archived. Level 2 achieved via independent reproduction of the Schlichting flat-plate boundary layer benchmark."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis required across at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI on QoI (RH index) must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "A mesh sensitivity study was performed using two mesh densities (4.2 M and 9.7 M cells). The coarse-to-fine RH index change was 3.1%, which the team interpreted as demonstrating adequate mesh independence. However, only two mesh levels were used; Richardson extrapolation requires a minimum of three refinement levels to compute a reliable observed order of accuracy and GCI. The absence of a third mesh level means the formal GCI cannot be computed and the achieved level remains at 1, one level below the MRL 2 requirement of 2. This shortfall was noted in the internal review but was not reflected in the factor status or the overall assurance declaration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances; fluid properties and boundary conditions must be recorded.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro tests were conducted with bovine blood at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C. Flow rates were set via calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5% FS). Rotational speed was servo-controlled (±10 RPM). All five COU operating points were replicated in the test rig. Condition equivalency is well documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or NRMSE) defined a priori; model predictions within acceptance band across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "The primary comparison metric was the normalised relative error on RH index. The acceptance band of ±15% was defined prior to data collection. Predictions at all 5 operating points fell within the band (max error 8.3%). A secondary comparison of hydraulic head within ±5% was also satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI used in validation must be directly related to the COU decision quantity; surrogate QoI must be justified.",
      "rationale": "The primary COU QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH. The validation QoI is also RH measured via the same NIH hemolysis protocol. There is no surrogate substitution. The direct correspondence between validation and COU QoI supports a level 3 rating."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
