    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; all seven are reported as meeting or exceeding their required levels. Six factors were scoped out as not applicable at MRL 2. Validation activities demonstrated RH index prediction error within the pre-defined ±15% acceptance band across all five COU operating points. The team concluded that the body of evidence is consistent with a Medium assurance level and that the model is fit for the stated purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
